# Coograph Conventions

This project ships with the Coograph AI coding template.

## Invocation

If the user types `/coograph-init` (or asks to "initialize the project", "set up coograph"), follow `.github/skills/coograph-init/SKILL.md` exactly.

## On session start

1. Read `.github/copilot-instructions.md` — full project conventions.
2. Read `.github/instructions/brutal-honesty.instructions.md` — communication style.
3. Check `openspec/changes/` for in-progress work (skip `archive/`).

## Code-graph first

ALWAYS use the code-graph (`get_minimal_context`, `query_graph`) before any codebase navigation. Fall back to `sqlite3 .code-graph/graph.db` only when the MCP server is unavailable. Fall back to grep/glob ONLY when the database is genuinely absent.

## OpenSpec gate

Any change modifying 2+ files, touching a spec, altering a public interface, or adding new behavior MUST go through `openspec/changes/<date>-<slug>/` with user approval BEFORE code. Exemptions are narrow: typo fix, comment-only edit, user-dictated config bump, follow-up on approved in-progress OpenSpec.

## Workflow

Plan → Propose (OpenSpec) → Apply → Quality Gates → Review Gate → Archive.

## Communication

Direct, evidence-based, severity-rated. Every finding cites `file:line` with verbatim quotes. No filler.
